    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="100"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d100">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/6–2944</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-29">June 29,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell rendition="#nowrap #top">Participants:</cell>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Secretary of State Hull,</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">General Shang, Chief of the Chinese Military
                            Mission, and</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Lieutenant Colonel Min-Hsien Lee, Aide-de-Camp to
                            General Shang</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>General Shang, Chief of the Chinese Military Mission, and Colonel Lee called to
                    pay their respects. General Shang urged the State Department to cooperate with
                    China in securing all possible airplanes, munitions and military supplies. I
                    told him that this had been the policy of the State Department from the
                    beginning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
